ay still be overlapping XOR conditions if data.record or the positive evaluation condition is also true.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The added branch is semantically appropriate, but the final XOR may become ambiguous when multiple conditions evaluate to true.\"\n        },\n        \"change_cost\": {\n          \"value\": \"low\",\n          \"reason\": \"Only one process change operation is required.\"\n        },\n        \"structural_quality_impact\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The repair is simple but may introduce overlapping XOR branch conditions, reducing the clarity and determinism of the decision structure.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"late\",\n          \"reason\": \"The change is applied at the final account-opening decision point.\"\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS3_sequentialize_rating_review_after_analysis\",\n      \"change_operations\": [\n        {\n          \"operation\": \"sequentialize_parallel\",\n          \"parameters\": {\n            \"first_activity_label\": \"analyze respondent bank annual report\",\n            \"second_activity_label\": \"Review Respondent Bank rating\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"substantial\",\n          \"reason\": \"Sequentializing the annual-report analysis and rating review removes the parallel context that may cause the rejected condition and the terminating branch to be interpreted as not reliably ordered. The existing rejected-rating branch still contains handle rejection followed by terminate.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The repair keeps the existing rejection-handling logic intact, but it changes the execution semantics by re