iness semantics are degraded because rejection handling is lost.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"The change is applied inside the rating-review rejection branch.\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS1_explicit_final_rejection_gate\",\n  \"best_resolution_reason\": \"RS1 is recommended because it provides the strongest compliance restoration while preserving the intended business semantics. It explicitly prevents account opening when the respondent bank rating is rejected and guarantees a terminating path after the rejected condition. Although it requires more operations than the simpler alternatives, it keeps the XOR decision structurally clean by avoiding overlapping branch conditions.\",\n  \"alternative_suggestion\": {\n    \"reason\": \"The provided operations do not support adding a formal boundary error event, escalation event, or explicit timeout/exception handler attached directly to the rating-review decision.\",\n    \"conceptual_solution\": \"Introduce a dedicated rejection-end event or exception transition directly associated with the rating-review XOR gateway, ensuring that whenever data.respondent_bank_rating == \\\"rejected\\\" becomes true, the process immediately follows a mandatory rejection-handling and termination path.\",\n    \"expected_compliance_impact\": \"This would fully satisfy the condition_eventually_follows requirement and make the compliance intent explicit at the modeling level.\"\n  }\n}",
